commit.message:
Do not set group of some files to root

There are a couple of reasons for that:
1. Some operating systems  (such as FreeBSD) do not have 
    group root (the root user is a member of the wheel group instead).
2. It makes packaging and testing out the installation
    as an unprivileged user a bit harder.
3. Those files will most likely get appropriate owner
    and group anyway during installation anyway.

commit.message:
Avoid install's -D flag to create directories

The -D flag is not supported by all install implementations.
For example, it is not present in FreeBSD's versions
of install. Let's use mkdir instead.

commit.message: reload logfiles, i.e. restart tail procs, on config change

Reset $! before check.

In general $! is only set by unsuccessful system calls.  If it is
used to check whether a system call has been successful, it has to
be cleared.  Otherwise any failed system call in the past may affect
the outcome.

Merge pull request #9 from bldewolf/fix-daemonizing

Daemonize earlier to avoid abusing root

Re-org priv drops to use EUID during setup

Instead of dropping all privs early or late, we drop everything early but only
set EUID to keep root in our back pocket.  Once we're happy with the setup, we
swap back to root, create the pidfile, then drop root privs for good.
Daemonize earlier to avoid abusing root
